<h3>Books&nbsp;</h3>
<p>The plague of disinformation is not new. In 1939, the journalist turned­educator, Clyde R. Miller, delivered a powerful lecture, ‘How to detect and analyse propaganda. His major recommen­dations remain valid today.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>He said: “There are three ways to deal with propaganda —1 suppress it; 2. try to answer it by counterpropaganda; 3. analyse</p>
<p>it.” He established the Institute for Propagan­da Analysis (IPA). The most potent tool of IPA was media literacy</p>